ifferent%20picture.%20Ellison%2C%20Wang%2C%20and%20Singh%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20the%20prosecutors%20in%20the%20case%20%E2%80%94%20cast%20Bankman-Fried%20as%20a%20monstrous%20villain%2C%20defense%20attorney%20Mark%20Cohen%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20trio%20of%20co-conspirators%20had%20their%20own%20culpability%2C%20repeatedly%20reminding%20the%20jury%20that%20they%20secured%20cooperation%20agreements%20with%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20wrote%20him%20into%20this%20movie%20as%20a%20villain%2C%20a%20bad%20guy%2C%20directing%20others%2C%20who%20apparently%20had%20no%20free%20will%20of%20their%20own%2C%20to%20steal%20billions%20of%20dollars%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20said%20of%20Bankman-Fried%20during%20closing%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20depiction%20of%20him%20made%20no%20sense%20in%20the%20real%20world%2C%20especially%20coming%20from%20these%20witnesses%20who%20were%20his%20closest%20friends%2C%20who%20knew%20him%20for%20years%2C%20who%20had%20gone%20to%20camp%20with%20him%2C%20to%20college%2C%20who%20had%20lived%20together%20with%20him%2C%20who'd%20worked%20with%20him%20for%20years%2C%20starting%20two%20businesses%2C%20who%20traveled%20with%20him%20and%20moved%20all%20over%20the%20world%20with%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20with%20someone%20you're%20now%20coming%20forward%20and%20saying%20is%20so%20terrible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20fourth%20witness%2C%20an%20FTX%20developer%20named%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-trial-former-roommate-adam-yedidia-immunity-testimony-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3EAdam%20Yedidia%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20testified%20under%20the%20condition%20of%20immunity%2C%20saying%20he%20feared%20he%20had%20%26quot%3Bunwittingly%20written%20code%20that%20contributed%20to%20the%20commission%20of%20a%20crime.%26quot%3B%20A%20fifth%2C%20FTX%20corporate%20counsel%20Can%20Sun%2C%20testified%20that%20Bankman-Fried%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20surprised%20at%20all%26quot%3B%20when%20Sun%20told%20him%20there%20was%20no%20legal%20defense%20for%20taking%20customer%20funds%20%E2%80%93%20deflating%20Bankman-Fried's%20claim%20that%20he%20had%20attorneys%20look%20over%20legal%20documents%20and%20thought%20everything%20was%20OK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20team%2C%20Angel%20said%2C%20was%20trying%20to%20%26quot%3Bblame%20everyone%20but%20their%20client%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20the%20co-conspirators'%20cooperation%20agreements%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edo%20little%20to%20detract%20from%20Bankman-Fried's%20culpability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20can%20always%20make%20the%20argument%20that%2C%20'Well%2C%20they're%20just%20trying%20to%20save%20their%20own%20skins%20by%20ratting%20out%20their%20boss.'%20But%20the%20reality%20is%20he%20was%20their%20boss%2C%20and%20they're%20all%20very%20knowledgeable%2C%26quot%3B%20Angel%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20people%20were%20literally%20living%20together%2C%20sleeping%20together%2C%20and%20operating%20everything%20together.%20It's%20pretty%20hard%20for%20SBF%20to%20make%20the%20case%20that%2C%20'Well%2C%20they%20did%20it.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20personal%20relationships%20and%20entanglements%20made%20the%20betrayal%20by%20Bankman-Fried%20that%20much%20more%20damning%20and%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20it%20to%20boomerang%20back%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBankman-Fried%20knew%20Wang%20and%20Yedidia%20from%20MIT%3B%20Singh%20was%20a%20family%20friend%3B%20Ellison%20was%20his%20on-again-off-again%20girlfriend%20he%20met%20at%20his%20first%20job%20out%20of%20college.%20They%20testified%20to%20respecting%20Bankman-Fried%20and%20trusting%20his%20judgment.%20When%20they%20thought%20his%20instructions%20were%20questionable%20(or%20unethical%2C%20or%20illegal)%2C%20they%20may%20have%20pushed%20back%2C%20but%20said%20they%20ultimately%20placed%20their%20faith%20in%20his%20seemingly%20reasonable%20explanations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22SBF%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653aabc40487ff031caf9467%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEllison%2C%20Bankman-Fried%2C%20Singh%2C%20and%20Wang.%20%3Cp%3EChelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Wang%2C%20Ellison%2C%20and%20Singh%20have%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20felonies%20and%20are%20awaiting%20their%20sentences%20after%20they%20cooperated%20in%20this%20trial.%20While%20Bankman-Fried%20faces%20over%20a%20century%20in%20prison%2C%20the%20co-conspirators%20could%20potentially%20dodge%20prison%20time%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELead%20prosecutor%20Danielle%20Sassoon%20said%20that%20Bankman-Fried%20thought%20he%20could%20%26quot%3Bget%20away%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BHe%20didn't%20bargain%20for%20his%20three%20loyal%20deputies%20taking%20that%20stand%20and%20telling%20you%20the%20truth%2C%20that%20he%20was%20the%20one%20with%20the%20plan%2C%20the%20motive%2C%20and%20the%20greed%20to%20raid%20FTX%20customer%20deposits%2C%20billions%20and%20billions%20of%20dollars%20to%20give%20himself%20money%2C%20power%2C%20influence%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20her%20closing%20argument.%20%26quot%3BHe%20thought%20the%20rules%20did%20not%20apply%20to%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBankman-Fried%20tried%20to%20flip%20the%20script%20but%20couldn't%20'recall'%20key%20details%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20hearing%20his%20ex-friends%20testify%2C%20Bankman-Fried%20made%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-ftx-testifies-criminal-fraud-trial-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erisky%20move%20to%20take%20the%20stand%20himself%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20tell%20his%20version%20of%20the%20story.%20He%20was%20polished%20when%20questioned%20by%20his%20own%20attorney%2C%20saying%20he%20should've%2