ied%20negotiating.%20I%20showed%20them%20an%20estimate%20I'd%20received%20to%20pack%20up%20my%20family%20and%20move%20us%20across%20the%20country%20with%20our%20livestock%20%E2%80%94%20it%20would%20have%20cost%20%24150%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20and%20asked%20what%20the%20relocation%20package%20would%20look%20like.%20I%20didn't%20get%20an%20answer.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20increased%20stress%20across%20teams%2C%20I%20found%20from%20talking%20to%20other%20people%2C%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20know%20that%20it's%20not%20true%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-wfh-productivity-impact-no-consensus-goldman-sachs-2023-8%5C%22%3Eproductivity%20decreases%20with%20work%20from%20home%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20then%20we%20were%20being%20told%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20the%20data%2C%20we%20just%20know%20it's%20true%26quot%3B%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20a%20phrase%20so%20patently%20un-Amazonian%20that%20it%20became%20hard%20to%20sit%20there%20and%20preach%20leadership%20principles%20to%20my%20direct%20reports%20amidst%20that%20messaging%20coming%20from%20the%20C-suite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20didn't%20make%20any%20sense.%20It%20still%20doesn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20after%20telling%20some%20of%20the%20members%20of%20my%20team%20that%20I'd%20be%20leaving%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20due%20to%20the%20RTO%20policy%20if%20I%20couldn't%20secure%20an%20extension%2C%20I%20ended%20up%20in%20a%20conversation%20with%20my%20manager%20where%20I%20expected%20to%20get%20fired.%20I%20started%20putting%20out%20applications%20to%20new%20jobs%20shortly%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20there%20were%20headaches%20there%3A%20personality%20conflicts%2C%20and%20tough%20salary%20negotiations%2C%20but%20the%20RTO%20policy%20was%20the%20sole%20reason%20I%20decided%20to%20leave%20Amazon.%20I%20wish%20I%20could%20have%20stayed%2C%20but%20it%20frankly%20felt%20intentional%20the%20way%20they%20were%20pushing%20people%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20excited%20about%20my%20new%20job.%20I'm%20working%20with%20a%20former%20Amazon%20colleague%20at%20a%20startup%20offering%20me%20roughly%20the%20same%20base%20salary%20as%20my%20prior%20job%20%E2%80%94%20though%20of%20course%2C%20they%20couldn't%20compare%20with%20the%20Amazon%20stock%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20while%20they're%20remote-first%2C%20if%20they%20ever%20decided%20to%20implement%20an%20in-office%20work%20policy%2C%20I'd%20find%20a%20new%20gig.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBrad%20Glasser%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Amazon%2C%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement%20that%20the%20company%20could%20not%20verify%20the%20above%20account%20after%20Insider%20declined%20to%20reveal%20the%20identity%20of%20its%20source%2C%20adding%20that%20a%20single%20anecdote%20cannot%20characterize%20a%20company%20of%20Amazon's%20size.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EGlasser%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BWe've%20repeatedly%20made%20our%20position%20clear%3A%20In%20February%2C%20we%20shared%20with%20employees%20that%20we'd%20be%20asking%20them%20to%20start%20coming%20into%20the%20office%20three%20or%20more%20days%20per%20week%20beginning%20in%20May%20because%20we%20believe%20it%20would%20yield%20the%20best%20long-term%20results%20for%20our%20customers%2C%20business%2C%20and%20culture.%20As%20part%20of%20this%20process%2C%20we've%20asked%20a%20relatively%20small%20percentage%20of%20our%20team%20to%20relocate%20to%20be%20in%20the%20same%20location%20as%20their%20teams.%20This%20isn't%20a%20one-size-fit-all%20approach%2C%20so%20team%20hubs%20and%20relocation%20timelines%20will%20vary%20based%20on%20a%20number%20of%20factors%2C%20and%20we're%20communicating%20with%20employees%20individually%20and%20providing%20relocation%20support.%20As%20is%20the%20case%20with%20any%20of%20our%20policies%2C%20we%20expect%20our%20team%20to%20follow%20them%20and%20will%20take%20appropriate%20action%20if%20someone%20chooses%20not%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C