om%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firan-limiting-jailed-nobel-winner-narges-mohammadis-medical-care-over-hijab-refusal-family%2Famp_articleshow%2F104924344.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firan-limiting-jailed-nobel-winner-narges-mohammadis-medical-care-over-hijab-refusal-family%2Famp_articleshow%2F104924344.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Questions%20Anonymity%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20and%20Voters'%20Right%20to%20Information%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20third%20and%20concluding%20day%20of%20hearings%20on%20a%20batch%20of%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fincometaxindia.gov.in%2Fcommunications%2Fnotification%2Fnotificationso29_2018.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%202018%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Solicitor%20General%20for%20India%20Tushar%20Mehta%20continued%20his%20arguments%20in%20favour%20of%20anonymity%20of%20donors%20to%20politicians%20and%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYesterday%2C%20Mehta%20had%20argued%20that%20anonymity%20ensures%20that%20the%20donor%20does%20not%20face%20retribution%20or%20victimisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20the%20CJI%20had%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20problem%20with%20the%20scheme%20is%20that%20it%20provides%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Eselective%20anonymity%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20because%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20which%20has%20been%20authorised%20to%20issue%20and%20encash%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20comes%20within%20the%20purview%20of%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%E2%80%99s%20argument%20focused%20on%20three%20issues%3A%20How%20the%202018%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Edeliberate%20attempt%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20funding%20received%20by%20political%20parties%20is%20clean%20money%3B%20how%20the%20government%20curbed%20unclean%20money%20from%20the%20market%20through%20de-registration%20of%20shell%20companies%20that%20were%20used%20as%20a%20vehicle%20of%20political%20funding%20and%20lastly%2C%20maintaining%20the%20confidentiality%20of%20the%20donor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20Supreme%20Court%20Constitution%20Bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20Dr%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20and%20also%20comprising%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%2C%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%20are%20seized%20of%20the%20matter%20which%20senior%20advocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%20characterised%20as%20one%20that%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Egoes%20to%20the%20very%20root%20of%20our%20democracy%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20on%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Felectoral-bonds-case-supreme-court-begins-hearing-case-that-goes-to-the-root-of-democracy%2F%5C%22%3E%20Day%201%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20hearings%3Cb%3E.%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Mehta%20told%20the%20court%20that%20disclosure%20of%20a%20donor%E2%80%99s%20identity%20could%20disincentivise%20the%20whole%20process%20of%20political%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20moment%20such%20a%20disclosure%20is%20made%2C%20the%20scheme%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Efails%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20CJI%20sought%20to%20press%20the%20point%20and%20remarked%20that%20the%20moment%20a%20contribution%20is%20made%20to%20a%20political%20party%2C%20it%20comes%20to%20know%20if%20it%2C%20Mehta%20replied%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EWhat%20the%20donor%20wants%20is%20that%20the%20other%20party%20should%20not%20know.%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3ESuppose%2C%20as%20a%20contractor%2C%20I%20donate%20to%20the%20Congress%20Party.%20I%20do%20not%20want%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20to%20know%20because%20it%20might%20form%20a%20government%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20offered.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EContinuing%20from%20where%20he%20had%20stopped%20yesterday%20on%20the%20point%20of%20confidentiality%2C%20Mehta%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20decision%20to%20not%20disclose%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20donor%20was%20a%20decision%20that%20the%20Parliament%20thought%20was%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EThe%20lawmakers%20felt%20that%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20is%20the%20most%20incentivised%20way%20of%20black%20money%20generation%20and%20black%20money%20payment%20in%20the%20political%20process%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20about%20voters%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20information%2C%20asks%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Gavai%20asked%20Mehta%20to%20address%20how%20the%20anonymity%20in%20the%20scheme%20could%20be%20reconciled%20with%20voters%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20replied%20that%20purity%20of%20election%20trumps%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20voters%20about%20political%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20explained%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EVoters%20vote%20not%20based%20on%20which%20party%20is%20funded%20by%20whom%2C%20voters%20vote%20based%20on%20ideology%2C%20principles%2C%20leadership%20and%20efficiency%20of%20the%20party%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20assured%20the%20court%20that%20the%202018%20electoral%20scheme%20is%20%3Ci%3Ebonafide%20%3C%2Fi%3Eand%20the%20scheme%20is%20not%20designed%20for%20the%20ruling%20party%20to%20keep%20tabs%20on%20contributions%20to%20politicians%20and%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20asked%20Mehta%20if%20he%20meant%20that%20the%20ruling%20party%20does%20not%20know%20who%20their%20donors%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20replied%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EEvery%20party%20knows%20who%20their%20respective%20donors%20are%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20provision%20of%20confidentiality%20in%20the%20scheme%20protects%20other%20parties%20from%20knowing%20about%20the%20donations%20received%20by%20a%20particular%20political%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20termed%20this%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Eheart%20of%20the%20matter%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20Mehta%20sought%20to%20differentiate%20political%20donations%20from%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Edonations%20we%20make%20during%20a%20pilgrimage%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Felectoral-bonds-case-anonymity-is-to-protect-the-donor-says-solicitor-general-on-day-2%2F%5C%22%3E%20Day%202%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20hearings%2C%20he%20had%20described%20political%20funding%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Enot%20charity%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Emarket%20driven%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20to%20drive%20his%20point%20home%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EIn%20Shrinathji%20%5BTemple%5D%2C%20people%20may%20donate%20Rs%20100%20crore%20without%20any%20name.%20This%20would%20be%20an%20anonymous%20donation.%20That%20is%20idealistic%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20CJI%20put%20a%20spanner%20in%20the%20works%20of%20his%20argument%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EThat%20is%20not%20idealistic%20because%20the%20assumption%20is%20that%20the%20Almighty%20knows%20who%20has%20put%20money%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Khanna%20remarked%20that%20everyone%20seems%20to%20be%20omniscient%20about%20the%20donations%2C%20except%20the%20voter%20who%20has%20been%20deprived%20of%20the%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsiderations%20and%20counter-considerations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20said%20that%20some%20important%20considerations%20need%20to%20be%20kept%20in%20mind%20while%20dealing%20with%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20a%20need%20to%20reduce%20the%20cash%20element%20in%20the%20electoral%20process.%20Second%2C%20the%20need%20to%20encourage%20the%20use%20of%20authorised%20banking%20channels%20for%20donations.%20Third%2C%20the%20need%20to%20incentivise%20the%20use%20of%20banking%20channels%20with%20confidentiality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20these%20considerations%20must%20be%20balanced%20with%20the%20other%20two%20counter-considerations%20which%20are%2C%20the%20need%20to%20ensure%20transparency%20in%20political%20funding%2C%20and%20ensuring%20that%20the%20scheme%20does%20not%20result%20in%20legitimising%20kickbacks%20and%20%3Ci%3Equid%20pro%20quo%3C%2Fi%3E%20between%20power%20centres%20and%20benefactors%20of%20that%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20a%20balance%20has%20to%20be%20created%20by%20the%20legislature.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Khanna%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20there%20is%20a%20consideration%20of%20confidentiality%20which%20is%20conflicting%20with%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20scheme%20legitimising%20kickbacks%20and%20%3Ci%3Equid%20pro%20quo%3C%2Fi%3E.%20Both%20the%20two%20considerations%20must%20be%20balanced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20then%20read%20these%20considerations%20in%20respect%20to%20Section%20182%20of%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fhandle%2F123456789%2F2114%3Fsam_handle%3D123456789%2F1362%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Companies%20Act%2C%202013%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%202018%20scheme%20has%20removed%20the%20requirement%20on%20the%20cap%20of%20net%20profit%20under%20the%20Companies%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20amendment%2C%20corporations%20would%20not%20donate%20an%20amount%20exceeding%207.5%25%20of%20their%20net%20profit%20in%20a%20financial%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20averred%20that%20there%20was%20a%20legitimate%20reason%20why%20the%20cap%20was%20introduced%20under%20the%20legislation%20and%20why%20it%20has%20stood%20the%20test%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20asserted%20that%20it%20was%20because%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%20company%20was%20to%20carry%20business%20and%20not%20to%20donate%20to%20political%20parties.%20If%20the%20purpose%20is%20not%20to%20donate%20to%20political%20parties%2C%20they%20must%20donate%20in%20small%20amounts%20with%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Ealtruistic%20motive%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20answered%20this%20query%20and%20clarified%20that%20a%20non-profit%20company%20cannot%20donate%20because%20that%20would%20make%20it%20vulnerable%20to%20be%20used%20as%20a%20shell%20company%20for%20political%20donations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EIs%20the%20government%20making%20a%20statement%20that%20they%20will%20amend%20the%20Companies%20Act%20to%20revive%20profit%20percentage-based%20donations%3C%2Fi%3E%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20responded%20that%20bringing%20an%20amendment%20is%20in%20the%20legislative%20domain%20and%20he%20cannot%20say%20anything%20in%20this%20regard.%20He%20also%20informed%20the%20court%20that%20the%20cap%20on%20the%20amount%20companies%20could%20donate%20did%20not%20work%20because%20many%20shell%20companies%20were%20created%20because%20of%20it.%20These%20shell%20companies%20would%20then%20be%20used%20to%20make%20political%20donations%2C%20thus%20avoiding%20the%20profit-percentage%20based%20requirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%202018%20electoral%20scheme%20was%20to%20disincentivise%20the%20creation%20of%20such%20shell%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EWith%20the%20view%20to%20discourage%20creation%20of%20shell%20companies%2C%20we%20did%20this%E2%80%A6%20If%20companies%20want%20to%20donate%20more%20than%207.5%25%20of%20their%20net%20profit%2C%20let%20the%20discretion%20remain%20with%20them%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20pointed%20out%20that%20legislation%20such%20as%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F2435%2F1%2Fa1961-43.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Income%20Tax%20Act%2C%201961%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20be%20adequate%20to%20keep%20a%20check%20on%20the%20creation%20of%20shell%20companies%20through%20their%20internal%20mechanisms%20such%20as%20checking%20the%20degree%20of%20business%2C%20and%20examining%20capital%20flow%20and%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20reiterated%20the%20concern%20of%20the%20court.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20court%20respects%20the%20process%20adopted%20by%20the%20government.%20However%2C%20the%20scheme%20has%20to%20be%20narrowly%20tailored%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20it%20balances%20out%20all%20the%20considerations%20stated%20by%20the%20court%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Eproportional%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20pointed%20out%20that%20if%20companies%20wanted%20to%20donate%20more%20than%20the%20cap%20of%207.5%25%20of%20their%20net%20profit%20in%20a%20financial%20year%2C%20they%20would%20use%20cash%20and%20this%20would%20allow%20black%20money%20to%20come%20into%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20this%2C%20the%20CJI%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3E%5BBut%5D%20that%20is%20not%20to%20say%20that%20unclean%20money%20is%20not%20coming%20to%20the%20system%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20puncturing%20the%20bubble%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20being%20a%20panacea%20to%20black%20money-funded%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EScheme%20not%20guided%20by%20any%20ulterior%20motive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20sought%20to%20take%20the%20court%20back%20to%20the%20mandate%20of%20the%20scheme.%20He%20argued%20that%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20ensures%20that%20there%20is%20no%20anonymous%20money%20in%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EThe%20bond%20cannot%20be%20purchased%20everywhere%20and%20it%20cannot%20be%20deposited%20anywhere.%20Why%20this%3F%20The%20donor%20and%20the%20donee%20both%20must%20have%20a%20designated%20account%20and%20%5Bin%5D%20a%20designated%20branch.%20Why%3C%2Fi%3E%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%20can%20only%20be%20purchased%20from%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20know%20your%20customer%20(KYC)%20requirements%2C%20including%20providing%20an%20Aadhaar%20number%2C%20are%20mandatory%20while%20buying%20an%20electoral%20bond.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EOnly%20political%20parties%20registered%20under%20Section%2029A%20of%20the%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F2096%2F1%2FA1951-43.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Ci%3ERepresentation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20and%20securing%20not%20less%20than%201%25%20votes%20in%20the%20last%20general%20elections%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20or%20state%20legislative%20assembly%E2%80%A6%20shall%20be%20eligible%20to%20receive%20the%20bond.%20Bond%20shall%20be%20encashed%20by%20an%20eligible%20political%20party%20only%20through%20a%20bank%20account%20in%20the%20authorised%20bank.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EThere%20was%20an%20objection%20to%20the%201%25%20votes%20requirement%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20Dalit%20Panthers%20Party%20submission%20on%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Felectoral-bonds-case-anonymity-is-to-protect-the-donor-says-solicitor-general-on-day-2%2F%5C%22%3E%20Day%202%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%201%25%20votes%20requirement%20was%20discriminatory%20against%20parties%20like%20them%2C%20which%20represented%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Emarginalised%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EEarlier%2C%20when%20exemptions%20were%20given%20to%20political%20parties%2C%20there%20was%20some%20mushrooming%20of%20parties%20just%20for%20exemptions.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20requirement%20of%201%25%20votes%20is%20not%20unrealistically%20high%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mehta%20reasoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20since%20electoral%20bonds%20expire%20after%2015%20days%2C%20it%20acts%20as%20a%20check.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20limited%20period%20in%20which%20the%20bond%20can%20be%20encashed%20prevents%20potential%20kickbacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EElectoral%20bonds%20that%20have%20not%20been%20encashed%20within%2015%20days%20of%20their%20purchase%20are%20automatically%20deposited%20into%20the%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fpm-cares-fund-why-we-should-lift-the-veil-to-demand-accountability%2F%5C%22%3E%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Relief%20Fund%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20Mehta%20informed%20the%20court%20that%20India%20is%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%20international%20treaty%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Eeradication%20of%20money%20laundering%20and%20drug%20money%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20the%20court%20that%20under%20the%20treaty%2C%20India%20is%20supposed%20to%20follow%20certain%20conditions%20in%20order%20to%20ensure%20that%20it%20continues%20to%20get%20financial%20assistance%20from%20the%20World%20Bank%20and%20other%20international%20financial%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20conditions%2C%20Mehta%20stated%20in%20the%20court%2C%20is%20that%20clean%20money%20should%20be%20induced%20into%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20told%20the%20court%20that%20his%20junior%20advocate%20Kanu%20Agarwal%20would%20present%20the%20data%20on%20donations%20less%20than%20Rs%2020%2C000%20before%20the%202018%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Kanu%20Agarwal%20then%20briefly%20addressed%20the%20court%20to%20show%20that%20prior%20to%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20donations%20worth%20less%20than%20Rs%2020%2C000%20to%20political%20parties%20would%20not%20be%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPost%202018%2C%20these%20dubious%20contributions%20have%20gone%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20the%20court%20that%20this%20was%20problematic%20because%20the%20law%20stated%20that%20donations%20of%20less%20than%20Rs%2020%2C000%20need%20not%20go%20through%20the%20requirement%20of%20disclosure%20of%20the%20name%20of%20the%20donor%20or%20the%20donee.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAgarwal%20also%20informed%20the%20court%20that%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%2C%20took%20a%20principled%20stance%20that%20they%20will%20not%20accept%20contributions%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20but%20they%20continue%20to%20accept%20donations%20in%20amounts%20less%20than%20Rs%2020%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAttorney%20General%E2%80%99s%20submissions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAttorney%20General%20of%20India%20R.%20Ventakaramani%20addressed%20the%20point%20of%20whether%20the%20scheme%20violates%20Articles%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-14-equality-before-law%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%2527Protection%2520of%2520life%2520and%2520liberty%2C%2527%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2014%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-19-protection-of-certain-rights-regarding-freedom-of-speech-etc%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2019%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-21-protection-of-life-and-personal-liberty%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2021%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20whether%20it%20also%20undermines%20the%20basic%20structure%20doctrine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20argued%20that%20while%20the%20court%20must%20look%20at%20voters%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20information%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%2C%20which%20necessitates%20that%20availability%20of%20background%20of%20an%20electoral%20candidate%2C%20such%20as%20criminal%20antecedents%2C%20the%20necessity%20of%20making%20information%20on%20political%20donations%20must%20be%20looked%20at%20from%20the%20concrete%20purpose%20and%20its%20relevance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20purpose%20of%20maintaining%20confidentiality%20(of%20political%20donations)%20must%20be%20assessed%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20reasonable%20restrictions%20under%20Article%2019(2).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EElection%20Commission%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20has%20opposed%20the%202018%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20through%20a%20letter%20written%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20and%20Justice%20stating%20that%20the%20amendments%20under%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fincometaxindia.gov.in%2Fbudgets%2520and%2520bills%2F2017%2Ffinance-bill-2017.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Finance%20Bill%2C%202017%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%2C%20Income%20Tax%20Act%2C%201961%2C%20the%20Companies%20Act%2C%202013%20and%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffcraonline.nic.in%2Fhome%2FPDF_Doc%2FFC-RegulationAct-2010-C.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%2C%202010%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20have%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Eserious%20repercussions%2Fimpact%20on%20the%20transparency%20aspect%20of%20political%20finance%2Ffunding%20of%20political%20parties%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20advocate%20Amit%20Sharma%2C%20representing%20the%20ECI%2C%20brought%20the%20data%20on%20funds%20received%20by%20political%20parties%20through%20quantum%20electoral%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20data%20was%20not%20updated.%20He%20said%20that%20he%20did%20not%20bring%20the%20updated%20data%20citing%20an%20interim%20Order%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20clarified%20that%20they%20never%20ordered%20that%20the%20ECI%20should%20stop%20updating%20the%20data%20on%20the%20quantum%20of%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20has%20ordered%20the%20ECI%20to%20submit%20the%20data%20updated%20up%20to%20September%2030%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover%20within%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20has%20happened%20so%20far%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Day%201%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%2C%20representing%20the%20lead%20petitioner%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%2C%20challenged%20the%20amendments%20brought%20in%20through%20the%20Finance%20Bill%2C%202017%20to%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%2C%20Income%20Tax%20Act%2C%201961%2C%20the%20Companies%20Act%2C%202013%20and%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%2C%202010%20through%20which%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20was%20introduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20challenged%20these%20amendments%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20first%2C%20they%20violate%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20because%20access%20to%20information%20is%20a%20fundamental%20right%20and%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20goes%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20electoral%20bonds%20promote%20corruption%20as%20they%20are%20opaque%20and%20anonymous.%20The%20public%20does%20not%20know%20the%20source%20of%20the%20donation%20and%20its%20beneficiary.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20Bhushan%20claimed%20that%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Edestroys%20and%20disturbs%20democracy%20in%20the%20country%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EExplaining%20this%20submission%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EThe%20bonds%20do%20not%20allow%20a%20level-playing%20field%20between%20political%20parties%20which%20are%20ruling%20versus%20political%20parties%20which%20are%20in%20the%20Opposition%20or%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20independent%20candidates%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBhushan%20presented%20another%20statistic%20to%20support%20his%20argument%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EThe%20contribution%20by%20way%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20to%20just%20one%20party%20%5BBharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20or%20BJP%5D%20is%20more%20than%20Rs%205%2C000%20crore%20in%20a%20period%20less%20than%20five%20years%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20claimed%20that%20since%20the%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20in%202017%2C%20the%20contributions%20made%20to%20political%20parties%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20have%20exceeded%20any%20other%20method%20of%20donation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%20warned%20against%20allowing%20corporations%20to%20fund%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EThe%20moment%20you%20allow%20the%20corporate%20sector%20to%20donate%2C%20whether%20with%20transparency%20or%20without%20transparency%2C%20it%20is%20inconsistent%20with%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20corporate%20sector%20which%20is%20in%20the%20business%20of%20doing%20business%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Sibal%2C%20this%20goes%20against%20the%20memorandum%20of%20association%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20donation%20is%20without%20the%20consultation%20or%20consent%20of%20the%20shareholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20CJI%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20court%20is%20not%20dealing%20with%20the%20legality%20of%20corporate%20donations.%20The%20CJI%20added%20that%20the%20court%20can%20still%20consider%20the%20%E2%80%98consultation%20or%20consent%E2%80%99%20aspect%20of%20the%20corporations%20donating%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESibal%20argued%20that%20there%20is%20nothing%20in%20the%20scheme%20that%20shows%20that%20the%20donation%20has%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20the%20electoral%20process.%20He%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20there%20is%20no%20cap%20on%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20that%20can%20be%20donated%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Shadan%20Farasat%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%2C%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EDespite%20being%20a%20ruling%20party%2C%20we%20have%20taken%20a%20principled%20stance%20to%20not%20accept%20any%20electoral%20bonds.%20We%20have%20not%20taken%20a%20single%20rupee%20through%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20the%20last%20five-and-a-half%20years%20at%20much%20cost%20to%20us%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20argued%20that%20the%202018%20electoral%20scheme%20fails%20to%20pass%20the%20test%20of%20arbitrariness%20of%20Article%2014%20because%20the%20scheme%20takes%20away%20non-anonymous%20money%20and%20puts%20it%20as%20anonymous%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Nizam%20Pasha%20also%20argued%20that%20the%20scheme%20is%20manifestly%20arbitrary.%20He%20told%20the%20court%20that%20since%20there%20is%20no%20possibility%20of%20taking%20cash%20while%20purchasing%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20question%20of%20black%20money%20coming%20in%20the%20market%20does%20not%20arise.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Day%202%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Vijay%20Hansaria%20took%20the%20court%20through%20different%20amendments%20made%20to%20the%20Companies%20Act%2C%201956.%20He%20argued%20that%20back%20in%201960%2C%20corporations%20could%20only%20donate%20a%20cap%20of%205%25%20of%20their%20net%20profit%20or%20Rs%2025%2C000%20in%20the%20financial%20year.%20Corporations%20were%20also%20obliged%20to%20disclose%20the%20amount%20they%20had%20donated%20to%20political%20parties%20or%20individual%20politicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20with%20an%20amendment%20in%201969%2C%20corporate%20donations%20were%20completely%20prohibited.%20This%20ban%20was%20removed%20through%20an%20amendment%20in%201985.%20In%202013%2C%20Section%20182%20of%20the%20Companies%20Act%20provided%20for%20a%20donation%20amount%20of%20up%20to%207.5%25%20of%20the%20net%20profit%20of%20a%20company%20in%20the%20financial%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20company%20which%20had%20an%20existence%20of%20less%20than%20three%20years%20could%20not%20donate.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20corporation%20had%20to%20disclose%20the%20particulars%20of%20the%20amount%20and%20name%20of%20the%20political%20party%20to%20which%20it%20was%20donating%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Hansaria%2C%20all%20these%20conditions%20regulated%20corporate%20donations%20and%20ensured%20transparency.%20However%2C%20with%20the%20amendment%20in%202017%2C%20all%20these%20requirements%20have%20now%20been%20omitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Sanjay%20Hegde%2C%20representing%20a%20shareholder%20of%20a%20public-listed%20company%2C%20reiterated%20that%20he%20supports%20the%20arguments%20of%20the%20petitioner%20and%20asked%20for%20the%20court%20to%20pass%20directions%20to%20reduce%20opacity%20in%20the%20political%20funding%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20corporate%20donations%2C%20Hegde%20told%20the%20court%20that%20many%20companies%20do%20not%20even%20put%20their%20profit%E2%80%93loss%20statements%20in%20the%20public%20domain.%20Now%2C%20the%20law%20allows%20them%20to%20make%20donations%20in%20crores%20in%20complete%20anonymity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20advocate%20representing%20the%20Dalit%20Panthers%20Party%20argued%20that%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20is%20discriminatory%20because%20it%20states%20that%20only%20political%20parties%20that%20have%20received%20at%20least%201%25%20of%20votes%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20or%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20of%20the%20respective%20state%20can%20get%20donations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20argued%20that%20this%20has%20a%20disparate%20and%20severe%20impact%20on%20the%20party%20because%20more%20than%20any%20other%20political%20party%2C%20they%20espouse%20the%20cause%20of%20marginalised%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EThat%20way%2C%20this%20is%20a%20hostile%20discrimination%E2%80%A6%20There%20is%20no%20rational%20nexus%20%5Bwhy%20a%20party%20needs%20to%20get%201%25%20vote%20to%20be%20eligible%20for%20donations%5D%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Gavai%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EThere%20is%20a%20rational%20nexus.%20A%20political%20party%20must%20have%20at%20least%201%25%20votes.%20Tomorrow%2C%20you%20may%20have%20%5Bmerely%5D%20two%20persons%20%5Bsupporting%20you%5D%20and%20%5Bstill%20you%5D%20may%20claim%20donations%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20pointed%20out%20that%20a%20party%20with%20less%20than%201%25%20votes%20could%20still%20receive%20donations.%20The%20court%20clarified%20that%20the%20current%20issue%20pertains%20to%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20and%20the%20petitioner%20is%20free%20to%20approach%20the%20appropriate%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20scheme%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%202018%20scheme%20notified%20by%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%2C%20an%20electoral%20bond%20is%20defined%20as%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EA%20bond%20issued%20in%20the%20nature%20of%20a%20promissory%20note%20which%20shall%20be%20a%20bearer%20banking%20instrument%20and%20shall%20not%20carry%20the%20name%20of%20the%20buyer%20or%20payee%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%20was%20notified%20by%20amending%20Section%2031%20of%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F2398%2F1%2Fa1934-2.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20Act%2C%201934%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20scheme%2C%20the%20bonds%20can%20be%20issued%20in%20the%20denominations%20of%20one%20thousand%2C%20ten%20thousand%2C%20one%20hundred%20thousand%2C%20ten%20hundred%20thousand%20and%20one%20crore%20rupees.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20scheme%2C%20only%20those%20political%20parties%20registered%20under%20Section%2029A%20of%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%20and%20who%20have%20secured%20not%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20the%20votes%20polled%20in%20the%20last%20general%20election%20to%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%20or%20the%20legislative%20assembly%2C%20shall%20be%20eligible%20to%20receive%20the%20bond.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fdonor-anonymity-versus-voters-right-to-know-supreme-court-reserves-judgment-in-electoral-bonds-case%2F%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Leaflet.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698944490000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-sc-questions-anonymity-of-electoral-bonds-and-voters-right-to-information%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20three%20days%20of%20hearing%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%202018%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20reserved%20its%20judgment%20while%20directing%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20to%20produce%20data%20on%20the%20quantum%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20purchased%20till%20September%2030%20this%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-sc-questi