20poets%20and%20tyrants.%20The%20truth%20gives%20way%20to%20inventions%2C%20some%20memorable%2C%20others%20forgettable.%E2%80%9D%20This%20is%20a%20book%20about%20the%20fragility%20of%20human%20memory.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20immediate%20aftermath%20of%20the%20arrest%20of%20Osip%20Mandelstam%20in%20May%201934%2C%20Stalin%2C%20Moscow%20lore%20has%20it%2C%20had%20telephoned%20Boris%20Pasternak%2C%20probably%20in%20June%201934.%20The%20tyrant%20was%20in%20his%20lair%20in%20the%20Kremlin%20and%20the%20poet%20in%20his%20apartment%20in%20Moscow.%20The%20conversation%20lasted%20around%20three%20minutes%20and%20then%20Stalin%20hung%20up.%20When%20Pasternak%20tried%20to%20call%20back%2C%20he%20found%20that%20the%20number%20no%20longer%20existed.%20It%20had%20apparently%20been%20created%20in%20the%20Kremlin%20for%20that%20one%20phone%20call.%20The%20phone%20call%20created%20a%20stir%20in%20the%20literary%20circles%20of%20Soviet%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20one%20were%20prepared%20to%20believe%20what%20circulated%20in%20the%20literary%20circles%20and%20in%20the%20samizdat%2C%20then%20Stalin%20asked%20Pasternak%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20little%20time%20ago%20the%20poet%20Mandelstam%20was%20arrested.%20What%20have%20you%20to%20say%20to%20that%2C%20comrade%20Pasternak%3F%E2%80%9D%20A%20flabbergasted%20and%20probably%20frightened%2C%20Pasternak%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CMandelstam%20and%20I%2C%20we%20are%20very%20different.%E2%80%9D%20Or%20words%20to%20that%20effect.%20Why%20did%20Stalin%20call%20when%20he%20could%20easily%20have%20summoned%20Pasternak%3F%20Why%20the%20need%20to%20know%20what%20Pasternak%20thought%3F%20Was%20there%20in%20the%20phone%20call%20an%20implied%20(or%20not%20so%20implicit)%20threat%20or%20warning%3F%20Such%20questions%20continue%20to%20persist%20not%20the%20least%20because%2C%20according%20to%20Kadare%2C%20there%20are%20at%20least%2012%20versions%20of%20this%20three-minute%20phone%20conversation.%20These%20versions%20come%20from%20various%20sources%20%E2%80%93%20from%20Isaiah%20Berlin%20(the%20famous%20Oxford%20don%20who%20was%20viewed%20with%20great%20suspicion%20by%20the%20Soviet%20secret%20police%20and%20who%20reputedly%20smuggled%20the%20typescript%20of%20%3Cem%3EDoctor%20Zhivago%3C%2Fem%3E%20out%20of%20Soviet%20Russia)%2C%20the%20poet%20Anna%20Akhmatova%20and%20other%20reporters%2C%20witnesses%20and%20so%20on.%20The%20evidence%20is%20mostly%20second%2Fthird%20hand%20and%20hearsay.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Soviet%20regime%2C%20as%20has%20now%20been%20discovered%2C%20was%20scrupulous%20in%20keeping%20records.%20The%20archives%20do%20say%20that%20such%20a%20conversation%20between%20Stalin%20and%20Pasternak%20did%20take%20place%20on%20June%2023%2C%201934%3B%20it%20lasted%20between%20three%20and%20four%20minutes.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20words%20said%20by%20each%20participant%20are%20clearly%20evidenced%20and%20preserved%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kadare%20tells%20us.%20Can%20we%20trust%20the%20archived%20version%3F%20Historians%20tend%20to%2C%20since%20archival%20evidence%20is%20the%20staple%20of%20the%20historian.%20But%20archives%20can%20be%20biased%2C%20be%20one-sided%20and%20even%20be%20manufactured.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20324px)%2085vw%2C%20324px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02141833%2F51QccnH-bvL.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22324%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02141833%2F51QccnH-bvL.jpeg%20324w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02141833%2F51QccnH-bvL-194x300.jpeg%20194w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683146%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIsmail%20Kadare%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EA%20Dictator%20Calls%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3EHarvill%20Secker%2C%202023%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EKadare%20begins%20with%20the%20archival%20version%20according%20to%20which%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20secretary%20made%20the%20call%20and%20announced%2C%20%E2%80%9CComrade%20Stalin%20will%20speak%20with%20you%20now.%E2%80%9D%20Stalin%20then%20came%20on%20the%20line%20and%20asked%20Pasternak%20the%20question%20quoted%20above.%20The%20latter%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20know%20him%20only%20slightly.%20He%20is%20an%20Acmeist%2C%20but%20I%20belong%20to%20a%20different%20group.%20So%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20say%20anything%20about%20Mandelstam.%E2%80%9D%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20retort%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhereas%20I%20can%20say%20you%E2%80%99re%20a%20very%20poor%20comrade%2C%20comrade%20Pasternak.%E2%80%9D%20And%20abruptly%20terminated%20the%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20record%20announces%20an%20arrest%20even%20though%20it%20was%20already%20the%20talk%20of%20Moscow%20but%20gives%20no%20indication%20why%20Stalin%20wanted%20to%20talk%20to%20Pasternak.%20But%20most%20mystifying%20of%20all%20is%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20comment%20before%20he%20disconnected%20the%20line.%20What%20did%20he%20mean%3F%20We%20get%20a%20clue%20from%20the%20second%20version%20that%20Kadare%20narrates.%20It%20comes%20from%20the%20memoirs%20of%20Galina%20von%20Meck%2C%20who%20was%20Tchaikovsky%E2%80%99s%20great-niece%20and%20probably%20Mandelstam%E2%80%99s%20lover.%20She%20recalled%20that%20at%20a%20gathering%20of%20poets%20where%20she%20was%20the%20only%20outsider%2C%20a%20very%20upset%20Pasternak%20had%20appeared%20and%20had%20blurted%20out%2C%20%E2%80%9CSomething%20awful%20has%20happened%20to%20me.%20Awful!%20And%20I%20behaved%20like%20a%20coward.%E2%80%9D%20He%20went%20on%20to%20tell%20the%20gathering%20about%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20phone%20call%20to%20him.%20According%20to%20Pasternak%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20von%20Meck%2C%20he%20had%20given%20the%20following%20fumbling%20reply%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%20know%20best%2C%20comrade%20Stalin%2C%20it%20is%20up%20to%20you.%E2%80%9D%20In%20answer%20to%20this%2C%20Stalin%20said%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20a%20definite%20sneer%E2%80%9D%20(the%20words%20are%20von%20Meck%E2%80%99s)%2C%20%E2%80%9CIs%20that%20all%20you%20can%20say%20%E2%80%93%20when%20our%20comrades%20were%20in%20tight%20spots%20we%20knew%20better%20how%20to%20fight%20for%20them%E2%80%9D%20and%20then%20put%20the%20receiver%20down.%20Was%20Stalin%2C%20through%20a%20seemingly%20innocent%20question%2C%20trying%20to%20implicate%20Pasternak%3F%20What%20would%20have%20happened%20to%20the%20latter%20if%20he%20had%20spoken%20in%20%C2%A0solidarity%20with%20Mandelstam%20and%20had%20condemned%20the%20arrest%3F%20Historians%20could%20also%20ask%20%E2%80%93%20Kadare%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%93%20did%20Stalin%20fight%20for%20his%20comrades%3F%20He%20fought%20against%20them%20%E2%80%93%20think%20of%20Trotsky%20in%20exile%20from%20the%20late%201920s%20and%20of%20Zinoviev%2C%20Kamenev%2C%20Bukharin%2C%20Preobrazensky%2C%20Radek%20and%20others%20already%20in%20disgrace%20when%20he%20is%20being%20holier-than-thou%20with%20Pasternak.%20Stalin%2C%20Kadare%20notes%2C%20if%20one%20goes%20by%20the%20second%20version%2C%20is%20actually%20humiliating%20Pasternak.%20But%20why%3F%20Kadare%20is%20justified%20in%20saying%20that%20the%20second%20version%20deepens%20the%20fog.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20nothing%20new%20in%20the%20third%20version%20which%20is%20a%20tape%20recorded%20conversation%20between%20two%20literary%20personalities%2C%20one%20of%20whom%2C%20S.P.%20Bobrov%2C%20was%20known%20for%20his%20malice%20towards%20Pasternak.%20However%2C%20when%20the%20issue%20of%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20fear%20is%20broached%20one%20of%20them%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CHe%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20been.%20However%20brutal%20Stalin%20may%20be%E2%80%A6still%E2%80%A6Stalin%20was%20the%20sort%20of%20person%E2%80%A6of%20course%20brutal%2C%20but%20still%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20Kadare%20comments%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20accursed%20%60but%20still%E2%80%99%20was%20usually%20a%20prelude%20to%20a%20tentatively%20prettified%20portrait%20of%20the%20dictator%2C%20and%20a%20corresponding%20denigration%20of%20the%20poet.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20version%20comes%20from%20Victor%20Shklovsky%2C%20another%20distinguished%20man%20of%20letters%2C%20who%20wrote%2C%20Pasternak%20%E2%80%9Chad%20correspondence%20with%20Stalin%2C%20talked%20to%20him%20on%20the%20phone%2C%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20defend%20Mandelstam%E2%80%9D.%20The%20words%20%E2%80%9Chad%20correspondence%20with%20Stalin%E2%80%9D%20inevitably%20raises%20the%20question%3A%20was%20there%20something%20more%20than%20a%20brief%20phone%20call%3F%20This%20version%20adds%20that%20Pasternak%20told%20Stalin%2C%20%E2%80%9CYosif%20Visarionovich%2C%20since%20you%20have%20phoned%20me%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20talk%20about%20history%20and%20poetry.%E2%80%9D%20Stalin%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20asking%20you%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20saying%20about%20Mandelstam%E2%80%99s%20arrest.%E2%80%9D%20So%20Stalin%20was%20not%20seeking%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20reaction%20but%20to%20find%20out%20what%20%E2%80%9Cthey%E2%80%99re%20saying%E2%80%9D.%20This%20version%20goes%20on%2C%20%E2%80%9CHe%20said%20something%20else.%20Then%20Stalin%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20they%20arrested%20friend%20of%20mine%2C%20I%20would%20bend%20over%20backwards%20to%20help%20him.%E2%80%9D%20Pasternak%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9Cif%20that%20is%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20phoning%20about%2C%20I%20have%20already%20bent%20over%20backwards.%E2%80%9D%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20parting%20shot%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20thought%20you%20were%20a%20great%20poet%2C%20but%20you%E2%80%99re%20just%20a%20big%20fraud.%E2%80%9D%E2%80%9D%20The%20conversation%20ended%20and%20Pasternak%2C%20according%20to%20this%20version%2C%20wept.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fifth%20take%20is%20from%20Nikolai%20Vilmont%2C%20a%20person%20very%20close%20to%20Pasternak%20in%201934%20but%20was%20no%20longer%20close%20to%20him%20when%20he%20recalled%20the%20incident.%20Vilmont%20claimed%20he%20was%20having%20lunch%20with%20Pasternak%20when%20the%20phone%20call%20came%20at%20around%204%20pm.%20The%20latter%20refused%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20great%20man%20actually%20wanted%20to%20speak%20to%20him%20so%20he%20was%20given%20a%20number%20to%20call%20back.%20When%20he%20dialled%20the%20number%2C%20Stalin%20spoke%20to%20him%20directly%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%E2%80%99re%20upset%20about%20your%20friend%20Mandelstam.%E2%80%9D%20Pasternak%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20never%20been%20real%20friends.%20More%20the%20opposite.%20We%20have%20different%20opinions.%20But%20I%E2%80%99ve%20always%20dreamt%20of%20talking%20to%20you.%E2%80%9D%20Stalin%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20old%20Bolsheviks%20never%20turned%20our%20backs%20on%20our%20friends.%20And%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20intend%20to%20talk%20to%20you%20about%20nothing.%E2%80%9D%20Vilmont%20could%2C%20of%20course%2C%20hear%20only%20hear%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20side%20of%20the%20conversation%20but%20he%20said%20that%20he%20had%20put%20down%20what%20Pasternak%20had%20told%20him.%20Once%20Stalin%20disconnected%2C%20Pasternak%20grabbed%20the%20phone%20to%20assure%20the%20former%20that%20Mandelstam%20really%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20his%20friend%20and%20that%20he%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20denied%20the%20friendship%20out%20of%20fear.%20But%20there%20was%20no%20reply%20from%20the%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20308px)%2085vw%2C%20308px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02142004%2FIsmail_Kadare_portret.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22308%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02142004%2FIsmail_Kadare_portret.jpeg%20611w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02142004%2FIsmail_Kadare_portret-260x300.jpeg%20260w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683147%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22356%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIsmail%20Kadare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20five%20versions%20do%20not%20show%20Pasternak%20in%20a%20good%20light.%20In%20the%20sixth%20version%20which%20comes%20from%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20Zinaida%20Nikolayevna%2C%20a%20different%20light%20emerges.%20Zinaida%20relates%20that%20she%20was%20ill%20and%20in%20bed%20when%20the%20call%20from%20the%20Kremlin%20came%20through.%20According%20to%20her%2C%20when%20she%20heard%20her%20husband%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CHello%20Yosif%20Visarionovich%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20blood%20went%20to%20my%20head%E2%80%9D%20but%20her%20husband%20remained%20calm%20and%20%E2%80%9Cspoke%20to%20Stalin%20in%20the%20same%20way%20as%20he%20would%20talk%20to%20me%20or%20you.%E2%80%9D%20Zinaida%20went%20on%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20realized%20from%20the%20first%20exchange%20that%20it%20was%20about%20Mandelstam.%20Borya%20said%20he%20was%20surprised%20at%20his%20arrest%2C%20and%20although%20there%20had%20been%20no%20great%20friendship%20between%20them%2C%20he%20valued%20his%20work%20writing%20as%20the%20work%20of%20a%20first-rate%20poet%2C%20and%20always%20recognized%20his%20merits.%20He%20asked%20Stalin%20to%20help%20Mandelstam%2C%20and%20if%20possible%20to%20release%20him.%20Borya%20spoke%20to%20Stalin%20plainly%20and%20directly%20without%20fine%20words%20or%20going%20into%20politics.%20I%20asked%20Borya%20how%20Stalin%20replied%20to%20his%20suggestion%20of%20talking%20about%20life%20and%20death.%20It%20turned%20out%20that%20Stalin%20said%20that%20he%20would%20talk%20with%20pleasure%2C%20but%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20to%20arrange%20it.%E2%80%9D%20In%20this%20telling%2C%20Pasternak%20had%20thus%20spoken%20to%20help%20a%20fellow%20poet%3B%20he%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20been%20flustered%20or%20frightened%3B%20the%20line%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20been%20abruptly%20cut%3B%20and%20there%20had%20been%20no%20attempt%20on%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20part%20to%20call%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20seventh%20version%20comes%20from%20the%20diary%20of%20the%20poet%2C%20Anna%20Akhmatova%2C%20who%20recorded%20that%20Mandelstam%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20Nadezhda%20(Nadya)%2C%20following%20the%20arrest%20of%20her%20husband%20had%20sent%20a%20telegram%20to%20the%20Central%20Committee.%20Following%20this%2C%20Stalin%20gave%20orders%20to%20have%20the%20matter%20looked%20into.%20Then%20he%20called%20Pasternak.%20Akhmatova%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20followed%20after%20is%20very%20well%20known%E2%80%A6Stalin%20reported%20that%20instructions%20had%20been%20given%20for%20everything%20to%20be%20straight%20regarding%20Mandelstam.%20He%20asked%20Pasternak%20why%20he%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20intervened.%E2%80%9D%20It%20would%20appear%20from%20this%20that%20the%20reason%20for%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20phone%20call%20was%20to%20assure%20Pasternak%20that%20matters%20were%20being%20set%20right%20and%20this%20could%20have%20happened%20earlier%20if%20Pasternak%20had%20intervened.%20Three%20years%20before%20her%20death%20(she%20died%20in%201966)%2C%20Akhmatova%20somewhat%20altered%20her%20version.%20According%20to%20the%20later%20version%2C%20Stalin%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20a%20poet%20friend%20of%20mine%20were%20to%20go%20to%20prison%2C%20I%20would%20move%20heaven%20and%20earth%20to%20save%20him.%E2%80%9D%20Pasternak%20replied%20that%20if%20he%E2%80%99d%20intervened%2C%20Stalin%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20agreed.%20Stalin%20then%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20he%E2%80%99s%20your%20friend%3F%E2%80%9D%20At%20this%2C%20according%20to%20Akhmatova%2C%20who%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20present%20during%20the%20conversation%2C%20%C2%A0Pasternak%20%E2%80%9Cshrivelled%E2%80%9D.%20Stalin%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20he%E2%80%99s%20a%20great%20poet%2C%20isn%E2%80%99t%20he%3F%E2%80%9D%20Pasternak%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CThat%20isn%E2%80%99t%20so%20important%E2%80%A6I%E2%80%99ve%20wanted%20for%20so%20long%20to%20talk%20with%20you.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20about%3F%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CAbout%20life%2C%20about%20death.%E2%80%9D%20At%20this%2C%20Stalin%20put%20down%20the%20phone.%20Akhmatova%20believed%20that%20Pasternak%20had%20been%20deliberately%20evasive.%20It%20should%20be%20noted%20that%20there%20were%20rumours%20in%20Russia%20that%20Anna%20and%20Pasternak%20had%20been%20lovers%2C%20even%20may%20have%20been%20husband%20and%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20eighth%20version%20from%20Mandelstam%E2%80%99s%20wife%20is%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20most%20sparse%2C%20not%20to%20say%20bleakest%2C%20account%20of%20the%20events%E2%80%9D.%20She%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CStalin%20began%20by%20telling%20Pasternak%20that%20Mandelstam%E2%80%99s%20case%20had%20been%20reviewed%2C%20and%20everything%20would%20be%20all%20right.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20strange%20reproach%3A%20why%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20Pasternak%20approached%20the%20writers%E2%80%99%20organizations%20or%20%60him%20personally%E2%80%99%20and%20why%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20he%20tried%20to%20do%20something%20for%20Mandelstam%3F%E2%80%9D%20According%20to%20Nadezhda%2C%20similar%20to%20Akhmatova%E2%80%99s%20diary%20record%2C%20Stalin%20did%20not%20call%20to%20seek%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20advice%20but%20to%20convey%20hopeful%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ninth%20version%20comes%20from%20the%20wife%20of%20the%20futurist%20poet%2C%20Sergey%20Bobrov%20who%20had%20himself%20recorded%20his%20version%20of%20the%20events%20(see%20the%20third%20version%20above).%20Bobrov%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20Maria%20Pavlovna%20Bogolovskaya%2C%20wrote%20she%20had%20gone%20to%20Pasternak%20to%20seek%20help%20for%20her%20husband%20to%20gain%20permission%20for%20a%20publication.%20On%20hearing%20the%20request%2C%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20face%20had%20%E2%80%9Cclouded%E2%80%9D%20and%20he%20had%20said%20he%20was%20unable%20to%20do%20anything.%20He%20had%20asked%20her%20if%20she%20knew%20about%20his%20conversation%20with%20Stalin.%20When%20she%20had%20said%20no%2C%20Pasternak%20had%20said%20it%20had%20been%20difficult%20for%20him%20to%20talk%20as%20there%20had%20been%20people%20in%20the%20house.%20When%20Stalin%20had%20asked%20him%20what%20he%20thought%20of%20Mandelstam%2C%20Pasternak%20told%20her%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20can%E2%80%99t%20talk%20about%20something%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20feel.%20It%20would%20be%20foreign%20to%20me.%20That%E2%80%99s%20what%20I%20said%20to%20him%2C%20that%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20say%20anything%20about%20Mandelstam.%E2%80%9D%20By%20this%20account%2C%20Pasternak%20felt%20nothing%20for%20a%20fellow%20poet%20and%20therefore%20saw%20no%20need%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20tenth%20version%20is%20from%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20lover%2C%20Olga%20Ivinskaya.%20She%20recorded%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20leader%E2%80%9D%20had%20spoken%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Crough%20voice%20using%20%3Cem%3Eti%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20he%20usually%20did%E2%80%9D.%20He%20had%20asked%20what%20the%20gossip%20was%20about%20Mandelstam%20in%20%E2%80%9Cyour%20literary%20circles%E2%80%9D.%20Pasternak%20had%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20no%20gossip%2C%20because%20to%20have%20gossip%20you%20have%20to%20have%20literary%20circles.%20But%20there%20are%20no%20literary%20circles%20because%20everyone%20is%20scared.%E2%80%9D%20At%20the%20other%20end%20there%20was%20a%20long%20silence%20and%20then%20Stalin%20had%20asked%20Pasternak%20what%20he%20thought%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20poet%E2%80%9D.%20Pasternak%20had%20replied%20that%20%E2%80%9Che%20and%20Mandelstam%20were%20poets%20going%20in%20totally%20different%20directions%E2%80%9D.%20Stalin%20replied%20in%20%E2%80%9Ca%20tone%20of%20contempt%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CSo%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20your%20friend.%E2%80%9D%20And%20put%20the%20phone%20down.%20At%20that%20moment%2C%20Pasternak%20confessed%20to%20Olga%20Ivinskaya%20%E2%80%9Che%20froze%20completely%E2%80%9D.%20The%20interesting%20detail%20here%2C%20as%20Kadare%20underlines%2C%20is%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20use%20of%20%3Cem%3Eti%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20was%20it%20a%20sign%20of%20intimacy%20or%20of%20contempt%3F%20It%20is%20the%20only%20testimony%20that%20mentions%20this%20detail.%20The%20other%20detail%20is%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20comment%20that%20fear%20had%20obliterated%20literary%20circles.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20penultimate%20version%20comes%20from%20Isaiah%20Berlin%20who%20claimed%20that%20Pasternak%20had%20spoken%20to%20him%20twice%20about%20the%20conversation%20with%20Stalin.%20Berlin%20wrote%20that%20Pasternak%20had%20initially%20thought%20someone%20was%20playing%20a%20prank%20on%20him%20but%20was%20convinced%20only%20when%20Stalin%20came%20on%20the%20line%20and%20explained%20that%20it%20was%20indeed%20Stalin.%20The%20latter%20asked%20Pasternak%20if%20he%20had%20been%20present%20when%20Mandelstam%20had%20read%20his%20%E2%80%9Csquib%20in%20verse%E2%80%9D.%20Pasternak%20said%20that%20this%20was%20of%20no%20consequence%20but%20he%20was%20happy%20to%20be%20talking%20to%20Stalin%2C%20he%20had%20always%20known%20this%20would%20happen%20and%20that%20they%20should%20meet%20%E2%80%9Cto%20discuss%20some%20matters%20of%20extraordinary%20importance%E2%80%9D.%20Stalin%20asked%20whether%20Mandelstam%20was%20a%20fine%20poet.%20Pasternak%20replied%20as%20poets%20they%20were%20entirely%20different%2C%20he%20felt%20to%20inner%20rapport%20with%20Mandelstam%20but%20he%20valued%20Mandelstam%E2%80%99s%20poems.%20According%20to%20Berlin%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20he%20related%20this%20episode%2C%20Pasternak%20plunged%20into%20metaphysical%20views%20about%20turning%20points%20in%20history%2C%20about%20which%20he%20wanted%20to%20talk%20to%20Stalin%20in%20a%20deep%20conversation%20of%20historic%20significance.%E2%80%9D%20Stalin%20ignored%20all%20this%20and%20repeated%20his%20original%20question.%20Pasternak%20too%20reiterated%20his%20desire%20to%20meet%20Stalin%20to%20talk%20about%20life%20and%20death%20and%20that%20such%20a%20meeting%20should%20not%20be%20put%20off.%20Stalin%20retorted%20with%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20I%20were%20Mandelstam%E2%80%99s%20friend%2C%20I%20would%20know%20how%20to%20defend%20him%20better.%E2%80%9D%20Berlin%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20entire%20story%20seemed%20to%20cause%20him%20great%20pain.%E2%80%9D%20Pasternak%20also%20told%20Berlin%20that%20when%20the%20phone%20call%20came%20only%20he%2C%20his%20wife%20and%20his%20son%20were%20in%20the%20apartment.%20This%20casts%20a%20serious%20doubt%20on%20the%20veracity%20of%20what%20Nikolai%20Vilmont%20(fifth%20version%20above)%20claimed.%20According%20to%20Vilmont%20the%20call%20had%20come%20at%204%20pm%20when%20he%20was%20having%20lunch%20with%20Pasternak.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%2012th%20retelling%20(if%20retelling%20it%20is)%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20tyrant%20was%20having%20fun%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20The%20author%20of%20this%20was%20the%20writer%20Vladimir%20Solovyev%20who%20was%20suspected%20of%20being%20a%20KGB%20agent%20and%20admitted%20to%20being%20one%20in%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20one%20to%20make%20of%20all%20this%3F%20It%20is%20too%20convenient%20to%20dismiss%20the%20episode%20and%20its%20many%20versions%20as%20a%20needless%20brouhaha.%20As%20students%20of%20history%20and%20of%20literature%20one%20cannot%20take%20such%20an%20evasive%20attitude.%20And%20Kadare%20doesn%E2%80%99t.%20He%20presents%20it%20as%20a%20riddle%20and%20interweaves%20it%20with%20many%20aspects%20of%20Russian%20and%20Soviet%20history%20and%20literature%20and%20his%20own%20dreams%20and%20nightmares%20about%20living%20under%20a%20communist%20dictatorship%20in%20Albania.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20overwhelming%20question%20is%3A%20why%20did%20Stalin%20call%20Pasternak%3F%20There%20are%20two%20different%20answers%20that%20emerge.%20One%2C%20Stalin%20was%20probing%20%E2%80%93%20gossip%20in%20literary%20circles%20and%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20own%20position%20regarding%20Mandelstam%E2%80%99s%20arrest.%20And%20second%2C%20Stalin%20was%20passing%20on%20the%20information%20that%20he%20was%20setting%20things%20all%20right%20in%20the%20Mandelstam%20affair.%20There%20is%20one%20thing%20common%20to%20both%3A%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20chiding%20of%20Pasternak%20or%20sneering%20at%20him%20for%20not%20standing%20up%20for%20a%20fellow%20poet%2Ffriend%20and%20for%20not%20interceding%20on%20Mandelstam%E2%80%99s%20behalf%20directly%20with%20Stalin.%20Only%20in%20the%20version%20given%20by%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20wife%20is%20it%20said%2C%20that%20Pasternak%20asked%20Stalin%20to%20help%20Mandelstam.%20A%20related%20question%20refuses%20to%20go%20away%2C%20what%20was%20the%20reason%20for%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20remorse%20%E2%80%93%20he%20wept%2C%20he%20froze%2C%20felt%20pain%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20behaved%20like%20a%20coward%E2%80%9D%20and%20so%20on.%20Was%20it%20because%20he%20felt%20he%20had%20failed%20to%20help%20Mandelstam%20(then%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20wife%E2%80%99s%20version%20goes%20through%20the%20trapdoor)%20or%20because%20he%20felt%20he%20had%20been%20humiliated%20by%20Stalin%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20of%20humiliation%20raises%20the%20question%20of%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20Stalin.%20Did%20they%20personally%20know%20each%20other%3F%20Hence%20the%20phone%20call%3F%20Why%20did%20Stalin%20use%20the%20familiar%20%3Cem%3Eti%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%20Recall%20also%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20wife%E2%80%99s%20testimony%20that%20Pasternak%20spoke%20to%20Stalin%20as%20an%20equal.%20One%20version%20states%20that%20Pasternak%20had%20some%20correspondence%20with%20Stalin.%20This%20question%20acquires%20some%20importance%20because%20as%20Kadare%20informs%20us%20that%20in%201935%2C%20Pasternak%20had%20actually%20written%20to%20Stalin%20to%20release%20Anna%20Akhmatova%E2%80%99s%20husband%20and%20her%20son.%20This%20would%20suggest%20that%20he%20had%20some%20kind%20of%20access%20to%20Stalin.%20This%20also%20adds%20credibility%20to%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20reproach%20about%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20intercede%20on%20behalf%20of%20Mandelstam%20in%201934.%20When%20Pasternak%20did%20intervene%20in%201935%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20Akhmatova%2C%20Stalin%20responded%20positively.%20It%20also%20should%20be%20noted%2C%20as%20Kadare%20does%2C%20that%20Stalin%20was%20true%20to%20his%20word%20and%20he%20did%20release%20Mandelstam%20in%201934%20and%20the%20latter%20went%20and%20met%20Pasternak.%20But%20Pasternak%20said%20and%20did%20nothing%20when%20Mandelstam%20was%20arrested%20a%20second%20time%20in%201938%20and%20sent%20to%20the%20Gulag%20where%20he%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20a%20personal%20equation%20between%20the%20poet%20and%20the%20dictator%20gets%20a%20different%20dimension%20with%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20plea%20to%20discuss%20philosophical%20issues%20%E2%80%93%20life%20and%20death%2C%20turning%20points%20in%20history%20%E2%80%93%20with%20Stalin.%20This%20request%20is%20odd%20because%20it%20was%20well%20known%20in%20Bolshevik%2Fcommunist%20circles%20that%20philosophy%20was%20not%20Koba%E2%80%99s%20(as%20Stalin%20was%20fondly%20called%20by%20his%20comrades)%20strong%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20the%20relationship%20between%20Pasternak%20and%20Stalin%20it%20is%20worth%20recalling%20an%20anecdote%20that%20Kadare%20does%20not%20include.%20It%20was%20said%20that%20Pasternak%20had%20translated%20some%20well-known%20Georgian%20poets.%20Stalin%20had%20approved%20of%20those%20translations.%20And%20later%2C%20when%20Stalin%20found%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20name%20on%20a%20death%20list%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20practice%20to%20personally%20go%20through%20death%20lists%20and%20sign%20them%20%E2%80%93%20he%20put%20his%20pen%20through%20Pasternak%E2%80%99s%20name.%20His%20instructions%20were%2C%20%E2%80%9CDon%E2%80%99t%20touch%20the%20cloud%20gatherer.%E2%80%9D%20He%20did%20not%20do%20the%20same%20for%20writers%20like%20Isaac%20Babel%20or%20even%20for%20the%20Georgian%20poet%2C%20Titzian%20Tabidze.%20It%20is%20not%20unreasonable%20to%20assume%20that%20there%20must%20have%20been%20some%20affinity%20between%20the%20dictator%20and%20the%20poet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20no%20easy%20answers.%20In%20Kadare%E2%80%99s%20words%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20incident%20impresses%20upon%20us%20its%20impossibility.%20It%20strikes%20an%20alarm%20bell%20that%20will%20not%20let%20any%20human%20conscience%20rest%20easy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETyrants%20will%20always%20have%20their%20perverse%20fun%20playing%20in%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20zone%20of%20death%E2%80%9D%20(Kadare%E2%80%99s%20telling%20phrase)%20but%20poets%20even%20when%20they%20perish%20in%20the%20Gulag%20or%20reach%20for%20the%20phone%20hoping%20to%20call%20the%20tyrant%20have%20immortality%20thrust%20on%20them.%20Nadezhda%20Mandelstam%E2%80%99s%20memoir%20is%20called%20%3Cem%3EHope%20Against%20Hope%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Poets%20kindle%20hope.%20Tyrants%20breed%20despair.%20Thus%2C%20poets%2C%20Kadare%E2%80%99s%20writes%2C%20are%20%E2%80%9Cwithout%20end%E2%80%9D.%20In%20the%20words%20of%20Ecclesiasticus%20(44%3A15)%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20people%20will%20tell%20of%20their%20wisdom%2C%20and%20the%20congregation%20will%20shew%20forth%20their%20praise.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Frudrangshu-mukherjee%5C%22%3ERudrangshu%20Mukherjee%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20chancellor%20and%20professor%20of%20History%20at%20Ashoka%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698918007000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02142307%2FStalin-Pasternack.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fa-poet-a-dictator-and-the-fragility-of-human-memory%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ismail%20Kadare's%20'A%20Dictator%20Calls'%20brings%20out%20the%20fraught%20and%20often%20dangerous%20relationship%20between%20poets%2Fwriters%20and%20tyrants.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fa-poet-a-dictator-and-the-fragility-of-human-memory%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Harris%20and%20Sunak%20due%20to%20discuss%20cutting-edge%20AI%20risks%20at%20UK%20summit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698917803000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104913560%2Cimgsize-32208.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fharris-and-sunak-due-to-discuss-cutting-edge-ai-risks-at-uk-summit%2Farticleshow%2F104913534.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104913534.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EUS%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20and%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20are%20participating%20in%20a%20UK%20summit%20focused%20on%20addressing%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20advanced%20artificial%20intelligence%20(AI).%20The%20summit%2C%20held%20at%20Bletchley%20Park%2C%20began%20with%20an%20agreement%20signed%20by%2028%20nations%2C%20including%20the%20US%20and%20China%2C%20to%20collaborate%20on%20understanding%20and%20managing%20AI%20risks.%20The%20summit%20aims%20to%20foster%20dialogue%20and%20cooperation%20rather%20than%20impose%20binding%20regulations.Sunak%20is%20expected%20to%20provide%20further%20details%20on%20his%20proposal%20for%20a%20global%20expert%20panel%20on%20AI.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fharris-and-sunak-due-to-discuss-cutting-edge-ai-risks-at-uk-summit%2Farticleshow%2F104913534.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fharris-and-sunak-due-to-discuss-cutting-edge-ai-risks-at-uk-summit%2Famp_articleshow%2F104913534.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fharris-and-sunak-due-to-discuss-cutting-edge-ai-risks-at-uk-summit%2Famp_articleshow%2F104913534.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Putin%20signs%20bill%20revoking%20Russia's%20ratification%20of%20global%20nuke%20test%20ban%20treaty%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698917796000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104913618%2Cimgsize-571074.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fvladimir-putin-revokes-russias-ratification-of-nuclear-test-ban-treaty%2Farticleshow%2F104913528.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104913528.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EPresident%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20signed%20a%20bill%20to%20revoke%20Russia's%20ratification%20of%20the%20Comprehensive%20Nuclear%20Test%20Ban%20Treaty%20(CTBT)%2C%20citing%20the%20need%20to%20establish%20parity%20with%20the%20United%20States.%20The%20CTBT%2C%20adopted%20in%201996%2C%20bans%20nuclear%20explosions%20globally%20but%20has%20not%20been%20fully%20implemented.%20Russia's%20move%20has%20raised%20concerns%20that%20it%20may%20resume%20nuclear%20tests%20to%20deter%20Western%20military%20support%20for%20Ukraine.%20However%2C%20Russian%20Deputy%20Foreign%20Minister%20Sergei%20Ryabkov%20stated%20that%20Moscow%20will%20only%20resume%20tests%20if%20the%20US%20does%20so%20first.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fvladimir-putin-revokes-russias-ratification-of-nuclear-test-ban-treaty%2Farticleshow%2F104913528.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fvladimir-putin-revokes-russias-ratification-of-nuclear-test-ban-treaty%2Famp_articleshow%2F104913528.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fvladimir-putin-revokes-russias-ratification-of-nuclear-test-ban-treaty%2Famp_articleshow%2F104913528.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What's%20Holding%20Back%20the%20Military's%20Plan%20to%20Institute%20Integrated%20Theatre%20Commands%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02135719%2FF92K5a0XsAAs1Bq.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Progress%20in%20instituting%20Integrated%20Theatre%20Commands%20(ITC)%20by%20the%20Chief%20of%20Defence%20Staff%20(CDS)%20General%20Anil%20Chauhan%2C%20to%20augment%20inter-service%20synergy%2C%20is%20reportedly%20stalled%2C%20principally%20over%20the%20knotty%20and%20lingering%20issue%20surrounding%20the%20overall%20operational%20control%20of%20the%20proposed%20formations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20recent%20media%20reports%2C%20citing%20official%20sources%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Military%20Affairs%20(DMA)%20which%20General%20Chauhan%20heads%2C%20is%20also%20%E2%80%98re-evaluating%E2%80%99%20its%20earlier%20plans%20of%20creating%20three%20ITCs%20%E2%80%93%20one%20each%20for%20the%20northern%20and%20western%20borders%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20an%20overarching%20maritime%2Fpeninsular%20command-and%20opting%20for%20%E2%80%98additional%20others%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20latter%20provision%20is%20reportedly%20under%20consideration%2C%20primarily%20to%20%E2%80%98accommodate%20service%20interests%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20euphemism%20for%20senior%20service%20officers%20retaining%20their%20ranks%2C%20multiple%20privileges%20and%20perquisites%20which%2C%20other%20than%20existing%20exaggerated%20pomp%20and%20majesty%2C%20included%20exclusive%20use%20of%20aircraft%20and%20rotary%20assets%20by%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20cross-section%20of%20senior%20military%20veterans%20maintain%20that%20determining%20the%20overarching%20operational%20head%20of%20the%20ITCs%20remains%20the%20CDS%E2%80%99s%20principal%20challenge%2C%20before%20formally%20forwarding%20the%20architecture%20of%20these%20joint%20battle%20groups%20to%20the%20government%2C%20which%20was%20scheduled%20earlier%20for%20completion%20by%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20proposed%20structure%20of%20the%20theatre%20commands%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20finalised%2C%20there%20are%20some%20important%20issues%20where%20greater%20deliberation%20is%20required%2C%E2%80%9D%20declared%20military%20analyst%2C%20retired%20Lieutenant%20General%20H.S.%20Hooda%20in%20an%20analysis%20for%20the%20Delhi%20Policy%20Group%20think%20tank%20in%20August.%20The%20issue%20of%20how%20the%20command%20and%20control%20over%20the%20theatre%20commands%20will%20be%20exercised%20remains%20unclear%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOther%20veterans%2C%20declining%20to%20be%20named%2C%20said%20that%20this%20%E2%80%98ticklish%E2%80%99%20issue%20of%20operational%20control%20over%20the%20ITCs%20was%20posing%20%E2%80%98grave%20problems%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20it%20was%20collectively%20%E2%80%98hobbled%E2%80%99%20by%20hierarchical%20inter%20and%20intra-service%20rivalries%2C%20conflicts%20of%20interest%20and%20personal%20ambitions.%20%E2%80%9CCompeting%20interests%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20resolve%20this%20critical%20concern%20swiftly%2C%E2%80%9D%20admitted%20a%20retired%20three-star%20Indian%20Navy%20(IN)%20officer%2C%20requesting%20anonymity.%20It%20requires%20deftness%20and%20all-round%20placate-ability%20within%20the%20military%20to%20be%20agreeably%20resolved%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMatters%20at%20the%20outset%20had%20been%20complicated%20by%20dealing%20with%20the%20CDS%2C%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20post%E2%80%99s%20founding%20charter%20in%20December%202019%2C%20out%20of%20this%20operational%20equation%2C%20despite%20him%20being%20India%E2%80%99s%20senior-most%20soldier.%20Under%20his%20terms%20of%20employment%2C%20the%20CDS%20is%20denied%20any%20military%20command%2C%20including%20over%20the%20three%20Service%20Chiefs%2C%20and%20his%20remit%2C%20amongst%20a%20host%20of%20myriad%20other%20responsibilities%2C%20including%20prioritising%20materiel%20procurements%20and%20force%20modernisation%20is%2C%20as%20the%20sole%20provider%20of%20%E2%80%98impartial%20(military)%20advice%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20political%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F22171955%2FF8OlZAaXEAAeXHw.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F22171955%2FF8OlZAaXEAAeXHw.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F22171955%2FF8OlZAaXEAAeXHw-300x191.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F22171955%2FF8OlZAaXEAAeXHw-1024x653.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681288%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22765%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20with%20Army%2C%20BRO%20and%20ITBP%20personnel.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40narendramodi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EMedia%20reports%20also%20indicated%20that%20the%20role%20of%20the%20three%20four-star%20single%20service%20chiefs%20in%20the%20re-organised%20ITC%20milieu%2C%20which%20had%20earlier%20been%20envisaged%20as%20one%20merely%20encompassing%20recruiting%20and%20training%20manpower%20and%20logistically%20supporting%20it%2C%20too%20was%20being%20re-assessed.%20This%20review%2C%20prompted%20no%20doubt%20by%20the%20individual%20chiefs%20themselves%2C%20miffed%20at%20being%20sidelined%20to%20a%20secondary%20role%20in%20the%20overhauled%20higher%20defence%20management%20setting%2C%20supposedly%20aims%20at%20providing%20them%20with%20some%20%E2%80%98compensatory%E2%80%99%20operational%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20veterans%20argued%20that%20this%20would%20only%20further%20complicate%20the%20CDS%E2%80%99s%20task%20in%20finalising%20the%20ITCs%2C%20as%20conferring%20operational%20responsibilities%20upon%20these%20three%20service%20chiefs%20of%20staff%20in%20an%20exclusively%20multi-service%20environment%2C%20could%20end%20up%20not%20only%20impinging%20upon%20but%20also%20clashing%20with%20the%20battlefield%20authority%20of%20theatre%20commanders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlongside%2C%20the%20earlier%20proposal%20of%20having%20four-star%20ITC%20commanders%20%E2%80%93%20on%20par%20with%20the%20service%20chiefs%20%E2%80%93%20is%20also%20believed%20to%20have%20been%20shelved%2C%20as%20it%20was%20felt%20that%20such%20a%20move%20would%2C%20by%20default%2C%20have%20meant%20elevating%20the%20CDS%20to%20five-star%20or%20field%20marshal%20status.%20For%20now%2C%20however%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20the%20ITC%20commanders%20are%20likely%20to%20remain%20three-star%20officers%2C%20but%20independent%20%E2%80%93%20and%20yet%20not%20independent%20%E2%80%93%20of%20their%20senior%20in%20rank%2C%20four-star%20service%20chief%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVarious%20ITC%20models%20have%20been%20under%20consideration%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%3B%20but%20amazingly%20none%20had%20been%20finalised%20to%20meet%20the%202022%20deadline%20imposed%20on%20the%20first%20CDS%20General%20Bipin%20Rawat%2C%20who%20died%20in%20a%20helicopter%20accident%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20in%20December%202021.%20According%20to%20defence%20analyst%20Brigadier%20Rahul%20Bhonsle%20of%20the%20Security%20Risks%20Asia%20consultancy%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20all%20endeavours%20so%20far%20to%20formulate%20ITCs%20were%20an%20exercise%20in%20%E2%80%98reinventing%20the%20wheel%E2%80%99%2C%20leading%20only%20to%20recurring%20delays.%20Resistance%20from%20the%20services%20in%20this%20regard%20was%20also%20obvious%20in%20confirming%20the%20ITC%E2%80%99s%20unitary%20operational%20commander.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20parliament%20passed%20the%20Enabling%20Inter-Services%20Organisation%20(Command%2C%20Control%20%26amp%3B%20Discipline)%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20which%20provided%20inter-services%20commanders%20with%20disciplinary%20and%20administrative%20powers%20over%20multi-service%20personnel%20serving%20under%20them.%20This%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20had%20smoothed%20the%20way%20for%20the%20DMA%20to%20conclude%20its%20task%20of%20formulating%20ITCs%20in%20their%20entirety%20which%2C%20so%20far%2C%20it%20has%20failed%20to%20vindicate.%20This%20Bill%20also%20empowers%20the%20government%20to%20create%20additional%20organisations%20as%20required%2C%20thereby%20providing%20the%20DMA%20a%20clean%20slate%20to%20operationally%20structure%20the%20ITCs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMany%20veterans%20and%20analysts%20agreed%20that%20the%20projected%20ITC%20formations%20were%20%E2%80%98riddled%20with%20confusion%20and%20contradictions%E2%80%99%20at%20multiple%20levels%2C%20indicating%20that%20such%20a%20major%20transformation%20guaranteed%20to%20completely%20alter%20the%20Indian%20military%E2%80%99s%20overall%20composition%20forever%2C%20had%20entailed%20little%20or%20no%20credible%20planning.%20This%20was%20despite%20the%20creation%20of%20two%20multi-service%20organisations%20in%202001%20and%202007%20for%20the%20specific%20purpose%20of%20fostering%20%E2%80%98jointness%E2%80%99%20between%20the%20three%20armed%20forces%20once%20a%20CDS%20was%20appointed%2C%20which%20was%20in%20January%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20such%20recommendatory%20body%20was%20the%20Headquarters%20Integrated%20Defence%20Staff%20or%20HQ%20IDS%2C%20created%20in%20October%202001%2C%20following%20the%20recommendations%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98Group%20of%20Ministers%E2%80%99%20after%20the%201999%20Kargil%20war%20with%20Pakistan%2C%20with%20the%20responsibility%20of%20evolving%20the%20blueprint%20for%20tri-service%20cooperation%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20reforming%20numerous%20other%20inherent%20shortcomings%20to%20enhance%20operational%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccordingly%2C%20the%20IDS%20was%20given%20charge%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20first%20two%20tri-service%20commands%20of%20which%20the%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Command%20or%20ANC%20was%20one%20to%20safeguard%20India%E2%80%99s%20strategic%20interests%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20Region%2C%20by%20creating%20the%20potential%20for%20rapid%20multi-service%20deployment.%20The%20other%20was%20the%20Strategic%20Forces%20Command%20or%20SFC%2C%20tasked%20with%20the%20ownership%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20assets%2C%20deliverable%20by%20land-based%20mobile%20platforms%20and%20air%20and%20underwater%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Group%20of%20Ministers%20had%20reasoned%2C%20at%20the%20time%2C%20that%20being%20a%20mixed%20organisation%2C%20staffed%20by%20service%20and%20civilian%20personnel%2C%20HQ%20IDS%20would%20be%20able%20to%20integrate%20policies%20and%20doctrines%20of%20the%20individual%20services%20into%20joint%20documents%2C%20but%20little%20had%20since%20emerged%20or%20been%20achieved.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20IDS%20advanced%20its%20jointness%20agenda%20by%20promoting%20discourse%20on%20higher%20defence%20planning%20through%20the%20multi-service%20Centre%20for%20Joint%20Warfare%20Studies%20(CENJOWS)%20founded%20in%202007%20which%20too%20had%20proved%20disappointing%20as%20did%20three%20other%20service-specific%20think%20tanks%2C%20founded%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20(MoD).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20included%20the%20Centre%20for%20Air%20Power%20Studies%20or%20CAPS%20which%20came%20up%20in%202001%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Land%20Warfare%20Studies%20or%20CLAWS%2C%20created%20in%202004%2C%20while%20the%20National%20Maritime%20Foundation%20or%20NMF%20was%20the%20last%20to%20be%20inaugurated%2C%20in%202005.%20Additionally%2C%20the%2060-year-old%20MoD-financed%20Manohar%20Parrikar%20Institute%20for%20Defence%20Studies%20and%20Analyses%20(MP-IDSA)%20too%20does%20not%20seem%20to%20have%20provided%20a%20workable%20proposal%20for%20higher%20defence%20reforms%2C%20let%20alone%20ITCs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20several%20complex%20personnel%20and%20fiscal%20issues%20threaten%20the%20formation%20of%20ITCs%2C%20which%20have%20not%20received%20adequate%2C%20if%20any%2C%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20comprise%20the%20planned%20absorption%20into%20the%20ITCs%20of%20establishments%20like%20the%20Border%20Roads%20Organisation%20and%20the%20Indian%20Coast%20Guard%2C%20both%20managed%20presently%20by%20the%20MoD%20and%20Central%20Para%20Military%20Forces%20like%20the%20Border%20Security%20Force%2C%20Assam%20Rifles%20and%20the%20Indo-Tibetan%20Border%20Police%2C%20which%20are%20run%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs.%20Integrating%20all%20these%20organisations%2C%20albeit%20partially%2C%20into%20the%20ITCs%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20without%20problems%2C%20as%20it%20will%20entail%20service%2C%20salary%20and%20retirement%20matters%20that%20invariably%20present%20grave%20obstacles%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20litigious%20environment%20that%20take%20years%20to%20resolve%20and%2C%20in%20many%20instances%2C%20end%20up%20being%20financially%20depleting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20more%20critical%20issue%20and%20one%20that%20dominates%20discussions%20within%20the%20services%20and%20the%20DMA%20is%20of%20parity%20in%20status%20and%20seniority%20of%20military%20officers%20presently%20heading%20the%2017%20existing%20single%20service%20geographical%20and%20functional%20commands.%20These%20comprise%20seven%20each%20for%20the%20army%20and%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20(IAF)%20and%20three%20for%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20(IN)%2C%20all%20headed%20by%20a%20three-star%20officer.%20These%2017%20were%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20two%20tri-service%20commands%20mentioned%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20these%2017%20commands%20eventually%20being%20subsumed%20by%20three%2C%20four%20or%20even%20five%20ITCs%2C%20one%20immediate%20fallout%20will%20be%20the%20placation%20of%20around%2013-14%20three-star%20officers%2C%20who%20would%20be%20dispossessed%20of%20their%20elevated%20statuses.%20Additionally%2C%20some%2010-odd%20Principal%20Staff%20Officers%20(PSOs)%20at%20all%20three%20Services%20Headquarters%2C%20three%20vice%20chiefs%20and%20the%20IDS%20head%20would%20also%20need%20to%20be%20%E2%80%98adjusted%E2%80%99%20without%20losing%20their%20sheen%20and%20frills%20in%20the%20new%20ITC%20set-up%2C%20further%20engendering%20disaffection%20amongst%20senior%20military%20officers.%20Likewise%2C%20the%20numerous%20three-star%20Directorate%20heads%20at%20each%20service%20headquarters%20would%20also%20need%20to%20be%20similarly%20accommodated%20in%20this%20herculean%20ITC%20endeavour%2C%20albeit%20without%20rancour.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERetired%20Lt%20General%20Raj%20Shukla%20who%20headed%20the%20Indian%20Army%E2%80%99s%20Training%20Command%20in%20Shimla%20declared%20at%20a%20recent%20seminar%20organised%20by%20the%20Observer%20Research%20Foundation%20in%20Delhi%20in%20August%20that%20in%20the%20debate%20over%20the%20ITCs%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98services%20were%20behind%20the%20curve%E2%80%99.%20He%20also%20warned%20of%20%E2%80%98serious%20consequences%E2%80%99%20from%20China%20if%20India%20got%20this%20ITC%20concept%20wrong.%20Former%20IN%20Chief%20Admiral%20Arun%20Prakash%20concurred%2C%20declaring%20in%20the%20same%20discussion%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%98myopia%20and%20parochialism%E2%80%99%20within%20the%20armed%20forces%20over%20the%20ITCs%2C%20as%20the%20military%20was%20intrinsically%20opposed%20to%20reform.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20US%20theatre%20command%20model%2C%20on%20which%20the%20Indian%20ITC%20template%20is%20largely%20believed%20to%20be%20patterned%2C%20the%20chain%20of%20military%20command%20flows%20from%20the%20president%20to%20the%20secretary%20of%20defence%20and%20onto%20the%20theatre%20commanders%20and%20back.%20The%20latter%20were%20overseen%20by%20another%20four-star%20chairman%20of%20the%20Joint%20Chiefs%20of%20Staff%20who%2C%20like%20India%E2%80%99s%20CDS%2C%20performed%20an%20advisory%20role%20to%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20political%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20nativised%2C%20this%20concept%20would%20incorporate%20ITC%20commanders%20reporting%20directly%20to%20defence%20minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20who%20then%2C%20like%20the%20US%20defence%20secretary%2C%20would%20be%20the%20deciding%20operational%20authority%2C%20but%20obviously%20with%20no%20military%20or%20battleground%20experience%2C%20like%20the%20majority%20of%20his%20predecessors.%20To%20overcome%20this%20handicap%2C%20a%20former%20IN%20chief%20had%20recently%20even%20suggested%20appointing%20a%20defence%20minister%20with%20intimate%20knowledge%20of%20military%20affairs%20with%20multi-party%20consensus.%20But%20such%20a%20fantasy%20remains%20just%20that%2C%20as%20such%20reasoning%20could%20be%20extended%20to%20include%20the%20appointment%20profile%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20entire%20federal%20cabinet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02135655%2FF9XZ5mwbwAATvWn.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02135655%2FF9XZ5mwbwAATvWn.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02135655%2FF9XZ5mwbwAATvWn-300x159.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02135655%2FF9XZ5mwbwAATvWn-1024x542.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683133%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22635%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDefence%20minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20with%20CDS%20Anil%20Chauhan%20and%20Air%20Chief%20Marshal%20V.R.%20Chaudhari.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40HQ_IDS_India%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20the%20default%20option%20of%20revising%20the%20CDS%E2%80%99s%20charter%20and%20investing%20him%20with%20operational%20responsibility%20over%20the%20ITCs%20needed%20to%20be%20viewed%20with%20caution%2C%20warned%20Gen%20Hooda%20in%20his%20aforementioned%20analysis.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20political%20leadership%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20cautioned%20%E2%80%9Cmust%20decide%20on%20how%20much%20authority%20they%20wish%20to%20invest%20in%20a%20single%20(military)%20appointment.%E2%80%9D%20Such%20a%20decision%2C%20he%20added%2C%20would%20impact%20the%20nature%20of%20future%20civil-military%20relations%20and%20needed%20to%20be%20deliberated%20upon%20carefully.%20Gen%20Hooda%E2%80%99s%20caveat%20harks%20back%20to%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20when%20one%20of%20the%20principal%20arguments%20against%20appointing%20a%20CDS%20with%20operational%20authority%20was%20that%20it%20could%20have%20an%20%E2%80%98adverse%E2%80%99%20outcome%20that%20was%20analogous%20to%20%E2%80%98military%20upsets%E2%80%99%20that%20had%20occurred%20since%20Independence%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20neighbourhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20other%20measures%20under%20consideration%20by%20the%20CDS%20that%20were%20delaying%20the%20ITCs%E2%80%99%20formal%20announcement%20reportedly%20included%20the%20appointment%20of%20a%20vice%20CDS%20and%20deputy%20CDS%20to%20oversee%20assorted%20%E2%80%98verticals%E2%80%99%20in%20military%20planning%20like%20intelligence%20gathering%2C%20procurements%20and%20joint%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20the%20onus%20of%20concluding%20the%20ITC%20model%20in%20its%20fullness%2C%20especially%20its%20operational%20command%20and%20control%20framework%20is%20exclusively%20dependant%20on%20the%20DMA%20and%20the%20forces%20and%2C%20for%20a%20change%2C%20not%20on%20the%20political%20leadership%20which%20has%20green-lighted%20the%20entire%20ITC%20project%20and%20awaits%20the%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20now%20up%20to%20the%20DMA%20and%20the%20CDS%20heading%20it%20to%20justify%20their%20averred%20inclusive%20military%20planning%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698916252000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02135719%2FF92K5a0XsAAs1Bq.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire